Out of the Way (2006/I)
  
  PL: Arthur Berkeley has a secret: his computer has just crashed, taking with it
  PL: his much-anticipated novel - and he forgot to make a back-up. He and his
  PL: friend Victoria, an acclaimed poet, run an independent publishing company,
  PL: and they were depending on the sales of his novel to keep them in business.
  PL: Arthur meets Lisa, who promises to help him become famous as a writer. Lisa
  PL: and Arthur begin dating, but when Lisa's ex-boyfriend Liam shows up from
  PL: New York, determined to win her back, Arthur is afraid to tell her, or
  PL: anyone, the truth.
  
  BY: Neil McArthur
  
